THE WORST predictions for costs have not come to pass, partly because Russia is selling plenty of wheat. But plenty of food-price woe may still await. We examine the curious re-appearance of the polio virus in the West. And the trials of “Pink Sauce” reveal the perils of being a cottage-food producer—or consumer—in the social-media age. Runtime: 24 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn For full access to print, digital and audio editions of The Economist, subscribe here www.economist.com/intelligenceoffer